edu.uga.dawgtrades.model

Interface ObjectModel


  • public interface ObjectModel
    This is the interface to the Object Model subsystem. It includes operations to create, store, retrieve, and delete all entity classes in the DawgTrades data model. For some of the classes, certain operations are not necessary and they have been commented out. The interface includes the operations of the factory pattern for the entity classes.

      • createCategory

        Category createCategory(Category parent,
                      java.lang.String name)
                        throws DTException
        Create a new Category object and link it to its parent Category, if provided. The parent Category, if provided, must be a persistent object, i.e., the value returned by the isPersistent() method must be true.
        Parameters:
        parent - a parent Category; it must be persistent. If this argument is null, the new Category will be a root (top-level) category.
        name - a name of the new Category
        Returns:
        a new Category object.
        Throws:
        DTException - if there is a problem with the new object creation (e.g., the parent Category is not persistent).

      • createCategory

        Category createCategory()
        Create an empty Category object. This method can be used to create an "empty" modelCategory and also can be used to create a "shell" object by the persistence subsystem when creating a proxy object.

      • findCategory

        java.util.Iterator<Category> findCategory(Category modelCategory)
                                          throws DTException
        Return Categories satisfying the search criterion abstracted by the modelCategory. For example, if the modelCategory object isPersistent(), only one object with the given identifier is returned in the iterator. If the modelCategory is not persistent, but has a name, the category with the same name will be returned.
        Parameters:
        modelCategory - a Category object used as the search criterion; if null is given, all categories will be retrieved
        Returns:
        an Iterator Category objects satisfying the criteria of the argument modelCategory
        Throws:
        DTException - if there is a problem with locating the requested Categories

        name - a name of the Item
        description - a description of the Item
        Returns:
        a new Item object, classified into the given category and owned by the given user
        Throws:
        DTException - if there is a problem with the new object creation (e.g., the category or user is not persistent)

      • findItem

        java.util.Iterator<Item> findItem(Item modelItem)
                                  throws DTException
        Return Items satisfying the criteria of the modelItem. If the modeItem has a defined identifier (isPersistent), only the specific item is returned. The modelItem may specify a category and/or owner identifier, in which case all items in the given category and/or owned by the given user are returned.
        Parameters:
        modelItem - a model item to use in locating items. If null is given, all items will be retrieved.
        Returns:
        an iterator of the located Item objects
        Throws:
        DTException - if there is a problem with locating the requested items

      • createExperienceReport

        ExperienceReport createExperienceReport(RegisteredUser reviewer,
                                      RegisteredUser reviewed,
                                      int rating,
                                      java.lang.String report,
                                      java.util.Date date)
                                        throws DTException
        Create a new ExperienceReport object and link it to RegisteredUser objects, given as a reviewer and a reviewed. The given reviewer and reviewed objects, the two RegisteredUsers for which the ExperienceReport is recorded, must both be persistent, i.e. the value returned by the isPersistent() method must be true for both.
        Parameters:
        reviewer - a RegisteredUser who is recording the report; it must be persistent
        reviewed - a RegisteredUser on whom the report is recorded; it must be persistent
        rating - a rating of the reviewed RegisteredUser, which must be within 1 and 5 (best), inclusive
        report - comments on the reviewed RegisteredUser and the transaction
        date - a date of the report
        Returns:
        the new ExperienceReport linked to the two involved RegisteredUsers
        Throws:
        DTException - if there is a problem with the new object creation (e.g., either the reviewer or reviewed are not persistent, or the rating value is illegal).
